sequenceDiagram
    participant browser
    participant server

    browser->>server: GET /exampleapp/new_notes
    note over server
        Server creates a new note object.
        It adds it to an array called notes.
        This is saved as data.json.
    end note
    activate server
    server-->>browser: 302 redirect to /notes
    deactivate server

    browser->>server: GET /exampleapp/notes
    activate server
    server-->>browser: HTML code
    deactivate server

    browser->>server: GET /exampleapp/main.css
    activate server
    server-->>browser: main.css
    deactivate server

    browser->>server: GET /exampleapp/main.js
    activate server
    server-->>browser: main.js
    deactivate server

    note over browser
        Browser starts executing JS code.
        It requests JSON data from the server.
    end note

    browser->>server: GET /exampleapp/data.json
    activate server
    server-->>browser: JSON: [{"content": "HTML is easy", "date": "2023-1-1"}, ...]
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser executes the callback function that renders the notes.
